mvr                                   macro                                  mvr

NAME
     mmvvrr and uummvvrr - move a single motor relative to its current position

SYNOPSIS

     mmvvrr mmoottoorr rreellaattiivvee__ppoossiittiioonn
     uummvvrr mmoottoorr rreellaattiivvee__ppoossiittiioonn

DESCRIPTION

     The mmvvrr macro moves mmoottoorr to a position at rreellaattiivvee__ppoossiittiioonn from the
     current position.  If the motor is initially at position XX this macro will
     move the motor to XX ++ rreellaattiivvee__ppoossiittiioonn.

     The uummvvrr macro also moves the motor, but provides an updated display of the
     motor position on the screen while the motor is moving.  The update
     interval, in seconds, is set by the global variable UUPPDDAATTEE.

EXAMPLE

     mmvvrr tthh --11

